              heading: "Common Causes",
              paragraph:
                "The check engine light in Volvo vehicles is often triggered by a loose or faulty fuel cap, failing oxygen (O2) sensors, malfunctioning mass airflow (MAF) sensors, or issues with the catalytic converter. In turbocharged models like the T5, T6, and D4/D5 diesels, ECU errors, boost pressure faults, and exhaust gas recirculation (EGR) system failures are also frequent, especially in high-mileage or poorly maintained engines."
