              heading: "Repair Solutions",
              paragraph:
                "Inspect the turbocharger for oil leaks, shaft play, or compressor damage. Check all intercooler pipes, boost hoses, and vacuum lines for cracks or disconnections. Clean or replace the MAF sensor and fuel injectors. If the turbo is faulty, replace it with an OEM or reconditioned unit. After replacement, reset the ECU and perform a proper drive cycle to recalibrate boost pressure and restore full performance."
